  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    A[DNA Damage Event] --> B{Lesion Type?}\n    \n    B -->|Oxidized Base| C[8-oxoG, Thymine Glycol]\n    B -->|Alkylated Base| D[3-methyladenine, 7-methylguanine]\n    B -->|Deaminated Base| E[Uracil, Hypoxanthine]\n    B -->|Other| F[Various Base Modifications]\n    \n    %% Glycosylase Recognition\n    C --> G{Specific Glycosylase?}\n    G -->|MutM FPG| H[8-oxoG Recognition]\n    G -->|Nth Endonuclease III| I[Thymine Glycol Recognition]\n    \n    D --> J[AlkA Recognition]\n    E --> K[UNG Uracil Glycosylase]\n    F --> L{Damage Recognition?}\n    L -->|MutY| M[Adenine Opposite 8-oxoG]\n    L -->|Other Glycosylases| N[Specific Recognition]\n    \n    %% Base Excision Step\n    H --> O[N-Glycosidic Bond Cleavage]\n    I --> O\n    J --> O\n    K --> O\n    M --> O\n    N --> O\n    \n    O --> P[Abasic AP Site Formation]\n    P --> Q{Glycosylase Type?}\n    \n    %% Bifunctional vs Monofunctional\n    Q -->|Bifunctional| R[MutM/Nth \u03b2-Lyase Activity]\n    Q -->|Monofunctional| S[UNG/AlkA No Lyase]\n    \n    R --> T[3' Phospho-\u03b1,\u03b2-unsaturated Aldehyde]\n    T --> U[AP Lyase Cleavage]\n    U --> V[Single-Strand Break]\n    \n    S --> W{AP Endonuclease?}\n    W -->|Xth Exo III| X[5' AP Site Cleavage]\n    W -->|Nfo Endo IV| Y[Alternative 5' Cleavage]\n    \n    X --> Z[3'-OH and 5'-dRP Termini]\n    Y --> Z\n    V --> AA[/3'-Phosphate Blocking Group/]\n    \n    %% End Processing\n    AA --> AB[APE1/Nfo Phosphatase]\n    AB --> AC[3'-OH Group Restored]\n    AC --> Z\n    \n    %% Gap Filling Decision\n    Z --> AD{Repair Pathway?}\n    \n    AD -->|Short-Patch 1 nt| AE[DNA Pol I]\n    AD -->|Long-Patch 2-10 nt| AF[DNA Pol I Strand Displacement]\n    \n    %% Short-Patch BER\n    AE --> AG[dRP Lyase Activity]\n    AG --> AH[Remove 5'-dRP]\n    AH --> AI[Single Nucleotide Gap]\n    AI --> AJ[dNTP Incorporation]\n    AJ --> AK[Gap Filled]\n    \n    %% Long-Patch BER\n    AF --> AL[Strand Displacement Synthesis]\n    AL --> AM[2-10 Nucleotide Flap]\n    AM --> AN{Flap Processing?}\n    AN -->|Small Flap| AO[Pol I 5'-3' Exonuclease]\n    AN -->|Large Flap| AP[Additional Factors]\n    \n    AO --> AQ[/Flap Removed/]\n    AP --> AQ\n    AQ --> AR[Gap Filled Multiple nt]\n    \n    %% Nick Sealing\n    AK --> AS{Ligation Ready?}\n    AR --> AS\n    \n    AS -->|Yes| AT[DNA Ligase Recognition]\n    AS -->|No| AU[Additional Processing]\n    \n    AT --> AV{Ligase Type?}\n    AV -->|NAD+ Ligase LigA| AW[Adenylate Transfer]\n    AV -->|ATP Ligase LigB| AX[Alternative Ligation]\n    \n    AW --> AY[Phosphodiester Bond Formation]\n    AX --> AY\n    \n    AY --> AZ[Nick Sealed]\n    AZ --> BA[Repaired DNA Strand]\n    \n    %% Quality Control\n    BA --> BB{Repair Verification?}\n    BB -->|Correct| BC[Successful Repair]\n    BB -->|Incorrect| BD[Mismatch Detection]\n    \n    BD --> BE[Mismatch Repair Pathway]\n    BE --> BF[Secondary Correction]\n    BF --> BC\n    \n    %% Alternative Pathways\n    AU --> BG{Issue Type?}\n    BG -->|Blocked 3' End| BH[\\Polynucleotide Kinase/]\n    BG -->|Modified 5' End| BI[Additional Endonucleases]\n    BG -->|Complex Damage| BJ[Nucleotide Excision Repair]\n    \n    BH --> AS\n    BI --> AS\n    \n    %% Final Output\n    BC --> BK[Genome Integrity Maintained]\n    BK --> BL[Cell Survival]\n    BL --> BM[Replication Competence]\n    \n    %% Error Pathways\n    BJ --> BN[Switch to NER]\n    BN --> BO[Alternative Repair Mechanism]\n    \n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style B fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style G fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style H fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style I fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style J fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style K fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style L fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style M fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style N fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style O fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style P fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Q fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style R fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style S fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style T fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style U fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style V fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style W fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style X fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style Y fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style Z fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AA fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style AB fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AC fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AD fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AE fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AF fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AG fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AH fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AI fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AJ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AK fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AL fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AM fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AN fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AO fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AP fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AQ fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style AR fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AS fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AT fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AU fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AV fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AW fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AX fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AY fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AZ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BA fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BB fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style BC fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BD fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BE fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BF fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BG fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style BH fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style BI fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BJ fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BK fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style BL fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style BM fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BN fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BO fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff",
  "name": "Base Excision Repair (BER)",
  "notGates": 3,
  "notes": "Comprehensive model of E. coli base excision repair showing multiple glycosylases, both short-patch and long-patch pathways, quality control, and connections to other repair systems. Essential for publication as it demonstrates conserved DNA repair logic across all life.",
  "organism": "E. coli",
